cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the problem of designing attack algorithms to learn robust neural networks. It also involves optimization techniques to solve the problem of attacking a BNN, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper uses image datasets such as MNIST and Fashion-MNIST, which are commonly used in computer vision research, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). As the paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks, it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of optimization techniques to solve the problem of attacking a BNN may also place this paper under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
